{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb52245cc-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s464d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"464d"},"text":"§ 464d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional funds for training","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In fiscal year 2004 and thereafter, funds appropriated in this account shall be available, at the discretion of the Director, for the following: training United States Postal Service law enforcement personnel and Postal police officers; State and local government law enforcement training on a space-available basis; training of foreign law enforcement officials on a space-available basis with reimbursement of actual costs to this appropriation, except that reimbursement may be waived by the Secretary for law enforcement training activities in foreign countries undertaken under section 801 of the Antiterrorism and Effective Death Penalty Act of 1996 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s509"},"text":"28 U.S.C. 509","children":[],"tail":" note); training of private sector security officials on a space-available basis with reimbursement of actual costs to this appropriation; and travel expenses of non-Federal personnel to attend course development meetings and training sponsored by the Center."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb52245cd-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/90/tIV"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–90, title IV","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1151"},"text":"117 Stat. 1151","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb52245ce-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb52245cf-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb52245d0-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Funds appropriated in this account”, and “this appropriation”, referred to in text, mean funds appropriated under the headings “","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Federal Law Enforcement Training Center","children":[],"tail":"” and “"},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"salaries and expenses","children":[],"tail":"” of title IV of the Department of Homeland Security Appropriations Act, 2004, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/90"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–90","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 801 of the Antiterrorism and Effective Death Penalty Act of 1996, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/132/s801"},"text":"section 801 of Pub. L. 104–132","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s509"},"text":"section 509 of Title 28","children":[],"tail":", Judiciary and Judicial Procedure."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Center, referred to in text, means the Federal Law Enforcement Training Center.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb52245d1-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Department of Homeland Security Appropriations Act, 2004, and not as part of the Homeland Security Act of 2002 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb52245d2-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following prior appropriation acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/dJ/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, div. J, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/431"},"text":"117 Stat. 431","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/67/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–67, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-11-12"},"text":"Nov. 12, 2001","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/516"},"text":"115 Stat. 516","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/3/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(3) [title I]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2763"},"text":"114 Stat. 2763","children":[],"tail":", 2763A–127."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/58/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–58, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/432"},"text":"113 Stat. 432","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"